                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1282a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 10, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Department’s 23, July 1, noon, instructing you to inquire what are Paraguay’s
                    views regarding a suitable settlement of the incident. Now that Bolivian and
                    Paraguayan Ministers have been withdrawn from Asunción and La Paz, please
                    endeavor discreetly to obtain the views of Paraguayan Government as to how it
                    feels the matter can be straightened out and relations resumed. A similar
                    inquiry is being made at La Paz in order to see if there is anything the
                    neutrals can do to bring about the reestablishment of diplomatic relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
